4.What is typecasting?

  *Conversion of one datatype into another datatype  is called typecasting means whenever we need to convert from integer to character or character to float or character to integer in such cases we use typecasting.
  *There are 2 types of typecasting:
    1.Implicit typecasting -It can be done by compiler itself(Here lower end data assigned to higher end data).
    2.Explicit typecasting -we have done explicit typecasting forcefully(Here oppose to implicit conversion).


Eg:Implicit casting
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
int main() {
   int a=2;
   float b=2.3f;
   cout<<a+b;
    return 0;
}
